  "text": "As the second most abundant element, helium plays an essential role in astrophysics. Nevertheless, its spectrum is poorly understood. The faint He ii 4685.7Å line is of particular interest, since it is the only important He ii line that can be observed with ground-based telescopes allowing higher spectral resolution than currently achieved for EUV He ii lines from space: [CITATION_1] find that the SUMER spectrograph (designed for broad coronal lines) does not resolve the narrow emissions from cool prominences, even after application of a maximum instrumental profile.",
